{
  "stem": "11144.5",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But my husband had a problem with it, of bringing her here and he was, I guess, insecure to-- to set her up in her own apartment, or maybe he couldn't-- we couldn't afford it maybe at that time, you know, to set her up on her own.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he didn't feel that we should live together.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Or again, maybe he was scared of the responsibility of bringing her here.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So my mother was traveling really back and forth, staying half a year, staying three months, staying a year once, maybe, or close to a year until, well, 1980 my sister passed away.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my mother was really alone there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And at that time, after my sister passed away, I said, well, there's no way, you know?",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We have to bring her here.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And at that time, when I started filling out her papers for coming-- for her coming for good here, at that time, she got cold feet because there were the two granddaughters left with whom she was really very close.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And she didn't want to leave them because it was really a maid and the father.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So my mother stayed on to help to raise them, really.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She didn't live with them but she was there, and she was a substitute mother, I guess, to them.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And until about six years ago, when she was going on in age, and finally, I got her a green card, she came here.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She still hadn't liquidated her apartment in Poland.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was still her home.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But she was here with me, and it wasn't easy to be together.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] So she was-- she was with me then.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
